rComments: Had this prof a few years ago. Was quite tedious to deal with. Could be very fun at times, but his poor interpersonal skills and way of doing things took away from things and left a bad taste in my mouth. Worth tolerating if you have no other options available, but I would recommend someone else. I enjoyed his work on the emotion series, though.
Energetic and eager to help out. Will call you out if you don't do teh readings.
follows the stereotypical drama/poetry person. the blue hair, swearing, and  putting people down is a little unprofessional and is frankly quite annoying.

Had him as a TA and was not too fond of him. Didn't help at all in person but would rather communicate through email - not helpful. Seemed arrogant when asked for help in person. Communicating with him seemed extremely stressful and impossible at times...

He is a good professor and is very clear with what he wants and expects.  He is very clear in his teaching about what is good and what isn't and provides good feedback on assignments, he really tries not to be too negative.  He does mean well.  However, he could be a little more organized and needs to not swear in class.

Awesome Prof. He's funny, plus, he's a dj! Make sure to do your readings or you will struggle. He's extremely clear on what he expects from his students and helps out a lot. Always available during office hours and he lets you know exactly what is going to be on the exams.

Interesting character. Heavy on class discussion, so do your readings or he WILL call you out and make you look unprepared. Isn't afraid to shoot down you're opinion. Often unclear on what he's asking of you. Not the greatest.
